Subject: [Security-news] SA-CONTRIB-2013-036 - Zero Point
	- Cross Site	Scripting (XSS)

View online: http://drupal.org/node/1954588

  * Advisory ID: DRUPAL-SA-CONTRIB-2013-036
  * Project: Zero Point [1] (third-party module)
  * Version: 7.x
  * Date: 2013-March-27
  * Security risk: Moderately critical [2]
  * Exploitable from: Remote
  * Vulnerability: Cross Site Scripting

-------- DESCRIPTION  
---------------------------------------------------------

Zero Point is a theme which includes many options, ideal for a wide range of
sites. The theme does not escape user supplied text which creates a reflected
Cross site scripting (XSS) vulnerability in URLs. There are no mitigating
factors.


-------- CVE IDENTIFIER(S) ISSUED  
--------------------------------------------

  * /A CVE identifier [3] will be requested, and added upon issuance, in
    accordance with Drupal Security Team processes./

-------- VERSIONS AFFECTED  
---------------------------------------------------

  * zeropoint 7.x-1.x versions prior to 7.x-1.9.

Drupal core is not affected. If you do not use the contributed Zero Point [4]
module, there is nothing you need to do.

-------- SOLUTION  
------------------------------------------------------------

Install the latest version:

  * If you use the Zero Point theme for Drupal 7.x, upgrade to zeropoint
    7.x-1.9 [5]

Also see the Zero Point [6] project page.

-------- REPORTED BY  
---------------------------------------------------------

  * Dennis Walgaard [7]

-------- FIXED BY  
------------------------------------------------------------

  * Florian Radut [8] the module maintainer
  * Dennis Walgaard [9]

